    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-04-18T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-04-18T13:00:00-05:00" n="38"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d38">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">851G.01/4–1846: Circular telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Certain
                            <gloss type="to">Diplomatic and Consular Officers</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="34" xml:id="d38fn1">At Bangkok, Batavia, Chungking, London, Manila,
                        Paris, and The Hague.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-04-18T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 18, 1946—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Vietnam Republic’s President Ho Chi-minh requested US, UK and other recognitions
                    approximating French recognition as free state within French Union. UK
                    informally replied unable recognize because negotiations re Vietnam actual
                    status continuing.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
